# Sprint 16: Integration with popular task managers (Jira, ClickUp, Notion, etc.)
# S16.ptl

**Goal:** Integrate totem-view with popular task managers so users can link Totem tasks to external items (Jira issues, ClickUp tasks, Notion pages) and open them in one click. Optionally support one-way import or status sync. Start with one provider (e.g. Jira) as reference, then add ClickUp and Notion (or a generic "external link") so the pattern is reusable.

**Invariants:**
- `instances/totem-view/S05-INVARIANTS.md` — glass, modal/overlay, glass buttons and cards.
- `instances/totem-view/S06-INVARIANTS.md` — three-level display (boards → board → task), shared UI layer.
- `instances/totem-view/S08-INVARIANTS.md` — Vercel layout, API; serverless constraints. External API calls from serverless; no secrets in repo (env or secure store).
- S14 (if applied): integrations can be tenant-scoped (credentials per tenant).

**Source of truth:**
- Totem task: id, title, status, description (from .pd). External: provider (jira | clickup | notion), externalId or key, url. Link can live in task metadata (e.g. in .pd frontmatter or separate store). API returns task with optional integrationLink: { provider, externalId, url }.

**Gate:** LOCKED

## Track 1: Integration contract and link model
- task: S16-T1-IntegrationContract.pd
- task: S16-T2-TaskLinkStorage.pd

## Track 2: First provider — Jira
- task: S16-T3-JiraAuthAndClient.pd
- task: S16-T4-JiraLinkAndUi.pd

## Track 3: Second and third providers
- task: S16-T5-ClickUpNotionAdapters.pd
- task: S16-T6-IntegrationSettingsUi.pd

## Track 4: Optional sync
- task: S16-T7-OptionalImportOrSync.pd

---

**Result (sprint outcome):** Users can connect at least one task manager (Jira first; then ClickUp and/or Notion). Tasks can be linked to external items; "Open in Jira/ClickUp/Notion" in UI. Optional one-way import or status sync. S05/S06/S08 preserved.

**Invariants for next sprints:** Create `instances/totem-view/S16-INVARIANTS.md` only if new frozen decisions (e.g. integration API shape, provider list); otherwise keep linking S05 + S06 + S08.
